     <div type="encomium">
   <head>VPON THE SILENT WOMAN.</head>
   <l>HEare you bad writers, and though you not see,</l>
   <l>I will informe you where you happy bee:</l>
   <l>Prouide the most malicious thoughts you can,</l>
   <l>And bend them all against some priuate man,</l>
   <l>To bring him, not his vices, on the stage,</l>
   <l>Your enuie shall be clad in so poore rage,</l>
   <l>And your expressing of him shall be such,</l>
   <l>That he himselfe shall thinke he hath no touch.</l>
   <l>Where he that strongly writes, although he meane</l>
   <l>To scourge but vices in a labour'd scene,</l>
   <l>Yet priuate faults shall be so well exprest</l>
   <l>As men doe act hem, that each priuate brest,</l>
   <l>That <gap reason="illegible" resp="#pdcc" extent="3 letters">
         <desc>•••</desc>
      </gap>des these errors in it selfe, shall say,</l>
   <l>He meant me, not my vices, in the play.</l>
   <closer>
      <signed>
         <hi>FRANC. BEAVMONT.</hi>
      </signed>
   </closer>
</div>
